main event: On May 10, 1964, two witnesses observed a white object moving across the eastern sky in Warrensville Heights, Ohio.
interesting points: Witnesses were star-gazing when they first spotted the object,The object appeared stationary for about 10 seconds before moving,Under telescopic observation, it appeared as a rectangular object with four smaller nearby objects,The sighting lasted approximately 4 minutes and 32 seconds,Comparisons were made to first and second magnitude stars for brightness assessment.
sighted object: a white rectangular object with four smaller objects in close proximity
witness description: Two male amateur skywatchers aged 16 and 11
